  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a comprehensive hemolysis measurement campaign conducted across five operating points; the campaign is described throughout this package as providing controlled experimental reference data, with flow-loop measurements characterised by systematic variation of inlet flow rate and impeller speed. The activity generating the primary ValidationResult is thoroughly documented in the evidence record and cited at length in the rationale sections below.",
