    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/hemolysis-obs-study-result-01",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary hemolysis validation — flow-loop measurement campaign",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values at five operating points (2 L/min / 2500 rpm, 3 L/min / 2500 rpm, 4 L/min / 2500 rpm, 3 L/min / 3500 rpm, 4 L/min / 3500 rpm) were compared against physical measurements obtained from the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump flow-loop dataset. Predicted NIH agreed with measured NIH within ±15% at all five points; the relative hemolysis index RH remained below 1.0 at every condition, satisfying the acceptance criterion. The measurement campaign systematically covered the relevant operating envelope and included repeat measurements to characterise variability. Agreement between CFD and measurement data supports the conclusion that the model adequately represents pump-induced hemolysis for the stated COU.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Mean absolute relative error in NIH: 8.3%; RH < 1.0 at all 5 operating points",
